metadata.name: Glomularus #80
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Poem Of Atoms #33
metadata.description:
There is a force in the universe that binds everything together
It's a electronic web that connects everything in a delicate balance. 
Some call it fate. But few know the truth.
They are the lifeblood of our society, and they are what keep us moving forward. We are constantly surrounded by them, and they are always changing. It's not a force, it's an orbit. And the dots are the energy sources.

metadata.name: Impossible landscapes #34
metadata.description:
Impossible landscapes are generative loops and animated pieces creating a landscape with a digital painting effect.
The size, position and motion frequency of trails are generated for each token, along with the color theme.
You can press spacebar to stop the animation.

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Brussels (Belgium).

metadata.name: Oscillators #48
metadata.description:
Click anywhere on the oscillator to play/pause.

3 Rules of Oscillators:
RULE 1, Oscillators should be viewed on Desktop (this is due to the way an oscillator is formed, it requires the display density of the device to be 2 pixels).
RULE 2, Oscillators should be viewed live and not as static images.
RULE 3, Oscillators should be run with the sound on.

Press "S" to Save a version of the Canvas (must be in fullscreen mode)

You are in a dark cave in the Johto region, the year is 1999...

Two synthesizers play a graceful melody atop the shimmering sound of a french horn. A cello provides a deep and haunting counterpoint.

Created with Tone.js and p5js.

Thank you to https://github.com/nbrosowsky/tonejs-instruments for the french horn and cello samples.

metadata.name: NATURAL 01 #37
metadata.description:
NATURAL 01 are generative loops and animated pieces creating a fullscreen visual based on a noise. It’s the first part of a collection.
The size, position and motion frequency of trails are generated for each token, along with the color theme.  Movements are generated by a flow based on a noise.
You can press spacebar to stop the animation.

 Features :
	- Generated grid between 50 and 90 cols and rows
	- 2 kind of shapes (circles and squares) : sometimes it can be full of squares or circles 👀
	- Shapes can be stroked or filled : sometimes it can be full stroked or filled 👀
	- Direction : Motion based on sinus, cosinus or tan (« circular »)
	- Background color :  color randomly get from 1 of 148 color themes

Created by Quentin Hocdé, in Brussels (Belgium).

metadata.name: L-Template #692
metadata.description:
THIS IS NOT AN ARTWORK.

Instead: a framework to store artwork data components onchain by including them as features in the token's smart contract. The stored data are parameters of a Lindenmayer System, which is a formal grammar that was initially conceived of as a theory of plant growth. L-Systems can model complex forms of plants using relatively few simple rules. Custom rules are generated during the minting of each token, based on the transaction hash string. 

The idea is that each iteration of the artwork can be reproduced accurately using an L-System interpreter by accessing the tezos blockchain through the FxHash API (GraphQL) and interpreting token metadata.

Reusable template source: https://github.com/x-terrain/x-terrain.github.io/tree/main/L-Template

Part of an ongoing project with RefractionDAO

metadata.name: Pine Dream #121
metadata.description:
Pine dream by Asaf Slook (2022)

This work is an attempt to create a simple pen-like generated drawing, in a way that confuses the observer to perceive it to be a real unique hand-drawn piece.

Rare features:
- Lonely tree
- Static stroke
- Sunny day palette
- Dotted land
- Partial land
 
The best results are from 1000x1000 and above.

This work was created using p5.js and love :)
